thread.title: Fatima falls in volleyball quarterfinals

author: The Associated Press
title: Fatima falls in volleyball quarterfinals
text:
ST. PETERS, Mo. — The Fatima Lady Comets fell in two games Saturday to Lutheran: St. Charles in the quarterfinals of the Class 2 state volleyball tournament. 
Lutheran won by a score of 25-21, 25-16. 
Emily Keilholz totaled six points and six digs for the Lady Comets, while Courtney Wolfe had five assists, six digs and three kills. 
Also for Fatima, Kaitlin Peters finished with seven digs, while Tara Buthod had six digs and three kills. Kenadi Huhn had three kills and Megan Werdehausen had two blocks. 
Fatima opened action Saturday with a 25-17, 25-17 win against Cuba in the sectional round. 
Huhn had 11 kills, while Peters finished with 10 digs. Wolfe totaled 16 assists and nine points, while Werdehausen had four blocks. 
Fatima, second in Class 2 last season, ends its season at 21-12-4. ﻿
